{"word":"ὑπόχρεως","slug":"ὑπόχρεως","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπόχρεως</b></el> <el>(ὑπό-χρεως, ων,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:χρέος'><el>χρέος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>indebted, in debt</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>ὑπ. τινος</el> his <i>debtor</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of property, <i>involved</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>obaeratus</el>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ὑπ. φιλίας</el> <i>bound by ties of</i> friendship, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}